String functions :-
------------------
1) strlen() :- returns the length (number of characters) of string.

2) str_word_count() :- returns the number of words in a string.

3) strtolower() :- convert the string into lowercase letters.

4) strtoupper() :- convert the string into uppercase letters. 

5) strip_tags() :- function strips a string from HTML, XML, and PHP tags.

	Note: HTML comments are always stripped. This cannot be changed with the allow parameter.

	Note: This function is binary-safe.

6) strrev() :- function reverses a string.

7) strtolower() :- function converts a string to lowercase.

	Note: This function is binary-safe.

8) strtoupper() :- function converts a string to uppercase.

	Note: This function is binary-safe.

9) implode() :- function returns a string from the elements of an array.

10) explode() :- function breaks a string into an array of strings.

Note: The "separator" parameter cannot be an empty string.

Note: This function is binary-safe.

explode(separator,string,limit)

Parameter |	Description
--------------------------------
separator	Required. Specifies where to break the string
string	Required. The string to split
limit	Optional. Specifies the number of array elements to return.

Possible values:

Greater than 0 - Returns an array with a maximum of limit element(s)
Less than 0 - Returns an array except for the last -limit elements()
0 - Returns an array with one element

11) str_replace() :- This function replaces string .